### How It Works

The [visualizer.py](file:///e:/dependencies%20proj/depgraph/reporter/visualizer.py) generates a **self-contained HTML file** (~27KB) with embedded D3.js (loaded from CDN). No server needed — just open the file in a browser.

### Visual Design

| Element | Appearance | Size |
|---------|-----------|------|
| Service nodes | Blue circles (`#58a6ff`) | Radius: 18px |
| Package nodes | Green circles (`#3fb950`) | Radius: 7px |
| Critical conflict nodes | Red circles (`#f85149`) | Radius: 12px |
| Warning nodes | Orange circles (`#d29922`) | Radius: 12px |
| Normal edges | Dark gray (`#21262d`) | 1px width |
| Conflict edges | Red (`#f85149`) | 2px width |

### Interactions

1. **Hover** — Tooltip shows package name, type badge, and version info per service
2. **Click** — Isolates the clicked node and its immediate neighbors (everything else fades to 15% opacity)
3. **Double-click background** — Reset isolation, show all nodes
4. **Drag** — Move nodes; the force simulation adjusts
5. **Scroll/pinch** — Zoom (0.1x to 4x)
6. **Pan** — Click and drag on the background

### Force Simulation Parameters

```javascript
d3.forceSimulation(nodes)
    .force("link", d3.forceLink(links).distance(100))     // 100px link distance
    .force("charge", d3.forceManyBody().strength(-300))    // -300 repulsion
    .force("center", d3.forceCenter(width/2, height/2))    // Center gravity
    .force("collision", d3.forceCollide().radius(r + 5))   // Prevent overlap
```

